The organization is not unfamiliar with the unconstitutional use of anti-riot laws to stifle and prohibit free speech, as prosecutors in Coeur d'Alene, Idaho had to hide evidence and disobey orders from the court to achieve bogus convictions, which resulted in several pre-trial dismissals. Freedom of speech, expression, assembly, and self defense are vital to preserving justice, liberty, and order in this country. The fact that these rights are almost universally despised by the presiding regime and its prosecutorial attack dogs only indicates that the truth sides with patriots.

@PatriotFrontSightings ¬ª Thomas Rousseau interviewed by the Dutch Nationalist organization Geuzenbond. This six page interview is within Geuzenbond's Stormlamp magazine published every four months. The magazine's mission is in "spreading patriotism as far as possible" through attention given towards "culture, language, history and ideas from a patriotic point of view." In the interview, Rousseau answers questions on the founding of Patriot Front, its political ideology, historical figures venerated by the organization, forms of activism, political change, the roots of American identity, plans for the future, and more.

‚ÄúIf we are to save this nation we must not merely denounce the injustices, but embody the solutions. We won't be placated by a politician's promises for the next election. Our ambition for a better life for our countrymen will not wait for congressional convenience. It is not our task to settle for the lesser of two political evils. It is their job to represent us. Instead they represent their money and their lies. They will not save us, so we are forging a new kind of patriot that will. One loyal to race and nation, family and morality, prosperity and security, and who can stand against the whole world if that is what destiny demands.‚Äù üìçAustin, Texas

@PatriotFrontSightings ¬ª Washington County, Arkansas has moved to update their official seal with a ring of 13 stars. The judge proposing the addition states it is in reference to the 13 cities of the county, and perhaps it is also referential to the name of the county and the historical American significance of the symbol. Patriot Front ‚Äî very active in the cities of the county such as Springdale, Fayetteville, and Prairie Grove ‚Äî is used as a reason to exclude the stars from the logo. PF's use of the stars placed on the first flag of the American nation has apparently dominated their perception in the modern landscape.
